RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAND FOR FREEDOM tugged forward along the inside to stalk into the turn, pursued under snug restraint around the bend, tipped out entering the lane, took aim on the new leader from the four path in upper stretch, bid while hanging on his left lead at the furlong grounds and drove clear. CANAVALL briefly dislodged his rider in the post parade while remaining in the grasps of his pony-person, tracked in the four path, crept closer into the turn, bid at the five sixteenths pole, forged an advantage entering the lane, but was headed by an outer bidder leaving the furlong grounds and was second best. BLOCKED set the pace in the two path, but was headed by an outer bidder entering the lane and yielded through the final furlong. CREATIVE WAY broke outwardly at the start, bumped an outer foe and put another to tight quarters in the process, laid off of the pace into the turn, but was shuffled back behind a faltering foe passing the three furlong pole to be towards the rear turning for home, yet regained stride and ran on for a minor placing. VALE took contact to his hind quarters from an inner troubled rival at the start, raced off of the pace in the four path, took closer order with three furlongs to go, but floated to the five path entering the lane and tired. BUCKTOWN was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe before taking back from crowded quarters between them at the start, trailed in the aftermath, improved in the five path at the three furlong pole, but fanned to the six path entering the lane and lacked a rally. TALKSCHEAP transferred contact from an inner rival to an outer foe at the start, raced off of the pace in the three path and between horses, briefly trailed passing the three furlong pole, swung to the seven path entering the lane and failed to factor. SHOTSHELL raced prominently early on, but shifted inwardly while spooking and losing action leaving the chute, checked behind rivals with eleven sixteenths to go while chasing two wide and between horses, then backed out entering the turn and subsequently faltered. MISTER MULDOON stalked in the three path, pursued between horses into the turn, then weakened nearing the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAWJ (IRE) set the pace two wide into the first turn, cleared and crossed over exiting that bend, showed the way inside of an outer bidder around the far turn, spurted clear in upper stretch, maintained a clear advantage through midstretch and held well from an outer on-charging foe late. ELUSIVE PRINCESS (FR) stalked two wide, prompted around the far turn before bidding nearing the lane, but failed to keep pace with her inner counterpart in upper stretch and yielded between horses in the final furlong. SOUNDS OF HEAVEN (GB) tracked two wide and between horses down the backstretch, was roused for run among foes around the far turn, but lacked a response and failed to menace. LIGURIA raced at the rear in the three to four path and outside of rivals, swung to the seven path entering upper stretch but lacked a rally. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRST MISSION stalked along the inside, was blocked behind a wall of rivals while entering the lane in the three path, tipped five wide and between horses at the furlong grounds, then rallied to forge an advantage in the shadow of the wire. COMMANDPERFORMANCE laid off of the pace in the three path, tracked four wide into the far turn, ranged up to bid turning for home, vied and wrestled a narrow advantage at the furlong grounds, but was caught by an outer bidder nearing the wire. COOKE CREEK stalked two wide and between horses, chased in the three path around the far turn before fanning six wide in upper stretch, stayed on outside of rivals in the late stages in hopes of producing a bid, but just missed reaching place. CREATIVE MINISTER tracked in the three to four path early on, pressed three wide and between horses into the far turn, bid turning for home, vied through midstretch but was bested by outer rivals in the final sixteenth. KEYSTONE FIELD saved ground off of the pace, shifted to the three path approaching the furlong grounds and ran on. IMPLEMENTATION pressed the leader while rank in the three path around the first turn, settled and vied around the far turn before outer rivals bid turning for home, then yielded to them leaving the furlong grounds. ROMAN CENTURIAN trailed in the three path and failed to factor. AIRTIME set the pace along the inside, but was headed by a trio of rivals nearing the lane and weakened in upper stretch.
